;; ## When and how to run tests
;; - [‚àö] tests are run once
;; - [‚àö] tests have absolutely no impact (i.e. the macro expands
;;       to nothing) when configured for a production environment.
;; - [‚àö] tests are registered and/or run at load time or with eval according
;;       to the config.
;; - [‚àö] tests are run once every var has loaded to avoid introduce code
;;       ordering problems to the already overwhelmed programmer.
;; - [‚àö] `test!` can be used at load time to run the tests registered so far.
;; - [ ] works well with reload and var unloading (clojure.tools.namespace)
;; - [‚àö] when tests are run via the clj test runner or explicitly in the repl
;;       with the test! fn:
;;       - successes: reported.
;;       - failures:  reported.
;; - [‚àö] when tests are *implicitly* run from the repl:
;;       - successes: silenced.
;;       - failures: reported.
;; - [‚àö] effects can be run by putting '!!' before an expr, evaluating it
;;       without testing the result.

;; ## Test selectors
;; - The CLI runner should:
;;   - [‚àö] run all tests if no args are provided
;;   - [‚àö] otherwise proceed with a:
;;         - whitelist logic using one or more namespace selectors (the args):
;;           - [‚àö] a ns name
;;           - [‚àö] a ns glob ("my.ns.*")
;;           - [‚àö] a regex
;;           - [‚àö] a predicate fn
;;         - and a blacklist logic using these same selectors but:
;;           - [x] prefixed with "!" (ns name & ns globs only).
;;                 Clashes with bash special chars.
;;           - [‚àö] or by providing a sequence to an ":exclude" option
;; - The test! fn behaves the same but when no args are provided:
;;   - [‚àö] it runs tests for the local namespace if it possesses minitest tests.
;;   - [‚àö] it runs all the tests otherwise (for instance in the REPL from the
;;         "user" namespace).

